reviews.text: Love this beautiful park. Nice bathrooms. Nice neighborhood.
Always nice for our class reunion picnic.   Bathrooms are always very clean, as well. 👍
Lots of fun! The historical society is located in the center building in the center of the park.

Memorial Park is the heart of Claremont. Major events happen here from 5k races to the whole 4th of July extravaganza. Every day it's a pleasant park. Always clean.
4th of July in Claremont is a throwback to a simpler time. Memorial park is the staging grounds for the parade. There are booths from all the local vendors and a pancake breakfast. Kids and adults can ride their bikes or scooters or roller skates or whatever in the parade.  Always free and fun.
In the summer, the city fills the splash pool for toddlers to cool off in a safe shallow fountain.
It's a great place to grab a sandwich from Wolfes and have a picnic.
Fun place to bring the kids and grandkids for a fun day in the natural world of parks😎
Good place for a walk with strolley, or biking/ hiking. Nice playground area.
Nice neighborhood park with a woodsy feel that includes a paved walking trail, play area, pool and a amphitheater.

Its a very nice park. With walking trails and a huge field, that I used to play ball with the dog. She chased some deer it was fun and there's crows and birds all around. And everybody walks their dogs there. And i think theres a playground I didnt goto that side
Cool park to go to! They have some good music acts in the warmer seasons.

I  went last week and listened to the entire concert of Chico Huff. Loved the music,  sitting outside and just chilling. This week's concert was just coming to a halt due to rain, when I arrived at 7:30. Looking forward to more visits there,  since it has a nice relaxing vibe!!

This park is located in Landsdale. It has a small pond, pavilion, an elaborate playground and lots of trails. It is well maintained and clean. Walkways at the front of the park are paved and the others are crushed gravel. In the vast wooded area there are several wooden raised walkways over the shallow creeks. There is an interesting hill that overlooks the park. It has plenty of parking. A great place to walk the dog.

Small but adequate little park to enjoy a stroll on the tree lined path. It has a pond which probably houses some bass. It also has a playground for the kids and a pair of Binoculars to view the surroundings. Overall nice little park.
This park has a small trail for walking and kids play area. My kids enjoy playing here.. I enjoy the morning n evening walks on the trail..

This is a beautiful small neighborhood park. When I lived in North Wales, I would walk my dog to this park. I was happy to see people walking their dogs and cleaning up after themselves in this park today.
Spacious park, free to nature. Very open and calming. Also the pond has fish in it too

Tried to order online and it wouldn't process so when I called 15 minutes later they said it was too late to place a phone order, I would have to come in to the restaurant.  I received good service at the restaurant but the steak was tough and had a lot to gristle in it. My ribs however were good as were the garlic mashed potatoes.

Applebees is always a good choice with all the options available. What I love most is they have delicious low calorie options without sacrificing the quality or flavor. There are usually great drink specials as well. Don't forget the happy hour options either!

Normally don’t have problems with Applebee’s but this particular location did not impress or even fulfill its purpose. Stopped in after a day of travel and we were seated quickly and our food came out quickly but the boneless wings were completely uncooked on the inside. Manager finally came over and said he would take care of the meals but never came back to confirm it was taken care of or told the waitress it was taken care of. Employees were loud and yelling about shifts and schedules and using a table near ours as a break room table. It was very unprofessional and a disappointing evening.

We went before the dinner on hour, it was basically empty except for the bar area. We had all you could ear of chicken tenders, ribs, Fry's, and slaw and my daughter had the chicken alfredo. Service was very good and very attentive to our needs. Very good place to eat. Just off the interstate so easy access.
Food was ok, under seasoned. Had broccoli cheese soup (yummy) and bourbon chicken shrimp (less than yummy). Great service and fun atmosphere, though. I'll be back!

Second time at this Friendly's and not by my choice. Food quality is slightly better than what I'd imagine a prisoner in a state penitentiary gets and the portion size was very small on a large plate. "A basic sandwich with single layer of fries spread out on a large plate" small. Turkey BLT looked nothing like the menu picture. Took 2 bites and had it boxed to go. The picture I took is exactly what I received. Ice tea was watered down. Service didn't account for much. I felt like  my presence was hassle the moment I arrived.
Kid was happy with the brownie sundae. If it wasn't for their desserts this place wouldn't exist.

Family reunion with 17 adults and 4 children... they made plenty of room for us and were very attentive to our needs! Waitress was friendly and well organized. Food was great. The meal was a great way to reconnect with each other because of how well we were taken care of. Thank you Camp Hill!

We had a really nice dinner at Friendly's. Our waiter, Vito, was very kind, helpful and patient. The turkey burger I ordered was very tasty, as were the fries. My ice cream sundae was so delicious! Our order made it to the table quickly after ordering. We will eat at this Camp Hill Friendly's again!

My husband and I like to come here about once a month for our ice cream date. My go-to is Vienna Mocha Chunk but this last time I tried the Hunka Chunka PB Fudge sundae. A medium is HUGE. Awesome for the price. Our server Elizabeth is always super friendly and helpful. She always makes sure our food is done right the first time. Thanks again! See you next month!

Very good place to eat. Servers are just like the restaurant name Friendly. The server we had, Elizabeth, knew us from before. I was amazed as we haven't been there for awhile.
She was awesome. I would suggest this place to anyone.
I've always liked this place, it has a cool look and chill vibe. This visit I tried their impossible burger though, and it's pretty amazing. Because of this, I'm well on my way to becoming a regular!

Such a great and casual space! Great for a chill Friday night. They have a large selection on draft and I loved their ciders and wines. The menu selection is small but quality. BBQ wings were delicious.

Place is nice, the food is good and service fine. Decent cheese steak, good French fries. Prices are reasonable.  Plenty of parking. Pool table, daily specials, and trivia I think on Tuesday nights. Plenty of sports on multiple TVs. Recommended.

Mostly friendly staff, ever changing beer selection. Bartenders are intermittent. Some are really good, some are far more interested in socializing.
The regular menu is decent for standard pub grub, always with some vegetarian options. Specials are frequently bizarre, some are actually really good.
Beware the staff if you're headed anywhere. Many of the wait staff will bowl you over if you're in the way of what they're doing. Whoever the GM's girlfriend at the time is usually being the worst about that.
Good good.  Good beer.  Sometimes older cans, so check dates.

If you're looking for a delicious and authentic pizza in Cebu. This is the place! I highly recommend the Salmon Salad for a healthy starter and Gregorio pizza for the main course. Service is fast and staff are friendly.

It's a nice, uncrowded resto serving good Italian food with generous servings. Had a good early dinner with some friends and we had the place pretty much to ourselves. Service was quick and unobtrusive, though we had to ask for some utensils because they seem to have forgotten to provide us with some. Try the focaccia and aglio olio, which were my favorites.
Love their wood firez pizza :)
Place is not crowded and food is the best

Giuseppe Pizzeria & Sicilian Roast
The food is tasty delicious
God selection of wines, tea and coffee 
Smoking area outside with fan
Aircon inside with Free wifi
Looks at customers to see if any of them need something
Opens and greets the customer
Fast, efficient and overall quality service 
Can I please give them six stars

I love this place!! Authentic and super fresh ingredients and the restaurant is family run. The people are super nice and very helpful. I have been going to this spot since it opened. What a nice change from the fast food chains.

One of the top cheese steak places in the area. We frequent here a lot when we just want a quick bite. Friendly staff and the rest of the menu is decent too. With Large portions, you never leave hungry. Definitely a regular stop for us.
Best and largest cheese steaks outside (and in) Philly. Want a diverse hoagie try the belly buster to share. All yummy😀

This place is the best. Good food. Quick service......and Margie or Margaret...and Chelsea are the best gosh darn servers and cashiers this side of the Amazon River. These two will make you smile, laugh, and whatever else you need. Very accommodating.  Highly recommend trying Ray's out. 
I think her name is Margaret but I always forget. I will say this......I would marry her in a minute. We would have beautiful children. If you decide to dine there......tell her that I love her.
Absolutely fantastic cheese steaks from Ray's. Highly recommended that you try their famous cheese steaks!

安くて美味しい！
飲み放題付き3,000円のコースは、お料理もいっぱい出てきて、ボリューム満点！
とむや
飲み放題メニューも種類が豊富で、色々なお酒を試せたり、ノンアルメニューも多かったです
辛さも控えめで食べやすいし、テーブルにタバスコのようなソースもあったので、調整もできます
店員さんも感じ良かったです
居酒屋わやわやの姉妹店。熟成白神生ハムを売りにしている。単品699円テーブルサーブだと1000円。国産三元豚使用‼️添加物一切不使用‼️
3,500円のコースでお腹いっぱい食べられます。ただしハイボールは炭酸が抜けた感じでイマイチ

手軽にアジアン料理を食べられるお店です。
メニューが豊富で、何かしら好きなものにありつけます。
パクチー嫌いな人も楽しめます。
ただ、週末は予約しないと入れなさそうです。
飲み放題メニューも多く、料理のコスパも高い。平日の夜でも混んでいました。

Get the breakfast foods...the burrito is massive and delicious! The coconut French toast was phenomenal as well.  Though, you only seem to ever find grape jelly there? Why is that? Some of us need the mixed fruit or strawberry jelly 😁
The food is very good. The portions are just right if your hungry and the atmosphere is calming. 5 Stars for the waitresses too.
Great place for breakfast. Food and the service are top-notch. Pleasant atmosphere makes for an enjoyable meal.
Nice family run place. Good food and reasonable prices. I had the Monte Cristo. Tasted good. Place was full but not slow. Recommend it.
Nice little diner in the center of Lansdale.  Food is good for the price.  Easy to miss if you aren't familiar with it.

Did the Hibachi dinner. It was pretty typical for performance. The food was excellent and there was a very generous portion provided and everyone ended up taking home at least enough for lunch the next day.
You don’t leave here hungry, and the prices are definitely reasonable. Will go back again! Great service from a waitress named Moriah! Very thorough with no slip ups!! Tipped well of course ! 👍
Their sushi is the best around.  Prices are high but you have to pay for quality fish.  The Shrimp Tempura is absolutely fantastic and I definitely recommend it

My family usually come here on special occasions like after graduation ceremony and birthdays dinner. Hibachi is everyone's choice and we enjoy watching the cook's  skillful performance with food  and interaction with us. It has been almost 20 years since late 1990s.... The food and service is consistently great and very entertaining.

Went here with local family while visiting the area. We didn't have reservations but were early enough to grab a lounge table. Ordered Lobster Dynamite, spicy tuna, and vegetable roll to share with my sister. The rolls were very well loaded and nothing was skimped. Green tea ice cream was two large scoops. Everything was excellently prepared and presented. I can see why the tables were full. Oishii!

My sister for a cake from here and my boyfriend went to go pick it up. When he got there it took 10 minutes for a subway employee to help him out because there weren't any maggie moo employees there. Once he got the cake it looked horrific, it looked like a child wrote on it. My sister wanted to talk to a manager there was none, needless to say my sister had him return it so they could go to another maggie moo location. Maggie moo is our favorite ice cream stop and it is so disappointing that this happened. If you can't manage a location, close it down or you will just build bad rapport.

Cumberland Road DQ - whenever our family members come home to Bluefield, the Dairy Queen is our first stop!  Those hot dogs!!!  Casual atmosphere, great for families.  Burgers, best hot dogs ever, French fries, and lots of ice cream.  😋
The toasted bun hot dogs were great service could be better
Best hot dogs I have ever had 😍.
Loved my Slaw Dog and Fries! Best around!  Yum!  I also love the shaved ice in the soda!
Its DQ wonderful staff was great!

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

Had a nice meal of wings with my 11yo daughter on a late Saturday afternoon. The staff was friendly and welcoming, the food was very good, and the ambience was nice. Wings were great !!! We will definitely returm.
The Best Wings I ever had! The smoke adds another layer of flavor. Karaoke night was a lot of fun!
